        <div class="section">
            <h2>About Islam</h2>
            <p>Islam is a monotheistic religion founded in the early 7th century in Arabia by Prophet Muhammad. It is one of the major religions in the world with over a billion followers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Beliefs</h2>
            <p>Islam is based on five fundamental pillars: Shahada (faith), Salah (prayer), Zakat (charity), Sawm (fasting during Ramadan), and Hajj (pilgrimage to Mecca). Muslims believe in the Oneness of God (Allah) and the finality of Prophet Muhammad's prophethood.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Holy Quran</h2>
            <p>The Quran is the holy book of Islam, considered the literal word of God as revealed to Prophet Muhammad. It serves as the primary source of guidance for Muslims in matters of faith, ethics, and daily life.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Prophet Muhammad</h2>
            <p>Prophet Muhammad is the last prophet of Islam, who Muslims believe received revelations from Allah through the angel Gabriel. He is regarded as the perfect example for all Muslims to follow.</p>
